  "figure-18-7": (
    caption: [The life cycle of hookworms: a shelled embryo develops into a first-stage juvenile which is followed by two molts. The resulting third-stage juvenile enters developmental arrest until it reaches a new host (A to C). Human infection may be via the mouth (D) or skin (E). Juveniles migrate through the circulatory system to lungs (F), enter alveoli (G), and then reach the intestine where they mate (H).],
