    caption: [Life cycle of *Wuchereria bancrofti*: mosquito ingests microfilariae which penetrate mosquito gut wall and develop to infective juveniles. Juveniles escape from mosquito's proboscis when the insect is feeding and then penetrate wound. (A to C, Juveniles migrate to regional lymph nodes and develop to sexual maturity in afferent lymphatic vessels. Adult worms produce microfilariae, which enter blood circulation (D to G).],
